# Commit standard (OCS v1.0)

Apply to every commit message you write or propose.

## Shape

```
<type>(<scope>): <imperative summary, ≤72 chars, no period>

<why — motivation, 1-2 sentences>

<what — invariants, alternatives, level the diff doesn't show>

Refs: #123
Fixes: #789
Risk: <if destructive>
```

## Types

`feat fix refactor perf docs test style chore build ci revert`

## Subject rules

- Imperative mood: `add` not `added` or `adds`
- Lowercase first letter
- No trailing period
- ≤72 chars (aim ≤50)
- No emoji
- No " and " — split into separate commits

## Body rules

- Lead with why
- Wrap 72 (100 for URLs/paths)
- Don't restate the diff
- 2-4 paragraphs max
- No hype, no AI flourishes, no apologies

## Footer rules

- `Refs:` related issues
- `Fixes:` / `Closes:` closes an issue
- `BREAKING CHANGE:` major bump
- `Risk:` destructive ops, migrations
- `Verified:` how verified beyond test suite
- `Co-Authored-By:` authentic collaboration only

## Banned

- Emoji anywhere
- `Generated with Claude Code` / `Co-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>` (unless user explicitly requested for that commit)
- Marketing language: "powerful", "stunning", "best-in-class", "world-class"
- Bare `chore: misc`

## Atomicity

- One concern per commit
- Tests for behavior changes ship in the same commit
- Squash WIP before push to shared branches
